Submitting and processing of VAT returns in the Czech Republic
Unless otherwise provided by the law, the entrepreneur is obliged, even if no tax liability has arisen, to submit a VAT return on the form specified by the Ministry of Finance within 25 days of the end of the tax period.
The tax liability arises at the end of the period for lodging the VAT return. In accordance with law no 235/2004, VAT on imports of goods is excluded from this scheme. In this case, the due date of the tax is determined by the customs regulations.
If, as a result of above-average deductible input tax, a claim for reimbursement arises, this amount shall be refunded to the Taxable Person within 30 days of the fixing of the input tax deduction, without the need for an application to be made.
The period shall not be applied in cases where the tax administrator initiates a tax procedure with regard to the taxpayer's tax liability.
According to Section 73 (11) of law no 235/2004, the right to deduct input tax may be exercised at the latest with the regular tax return for the last taxable period of the calendar year in which the right to deduct input tax has arisen.
After the expiry of this period, the deduction of the input tax may still be claimed within three years of the end of the taxable period in which the claim would have been possible for the first time.
