Final remark
Through the collaboration, the objectives of the BRH and NKÚ were achieved.
Both sais gained in-depth knowledge of the systems of VAT administration in the Czech Republic and Germany.
The cooperation disclosed differences in the two systems and in the legal regulations governing VAT administration.
During the parallel tests, interesting cases of intra-community deliveries or acquisitions occurred.
Some of them are worth further observation.
On the basis of the audit results, both sais drew up recommendations for the management of VAT.
The follow-up of these recommendations in the Form of a control audit should be part of further observation.
The new experience and knowledge gained through the cooperation of both sais is the basis for the successful implementation of future audits in the field of Value Added Tax Administration.
